00:00:00,040 --> 00:00:14,740
( Watch on Kissasia.vip )

1
00:00:46,693 --> 00:00:49,654
<i>Eun Chae-ni, 27 years old.</i>

2
00:00:51,114 --> 00:00:53,116
<i>A trainwreck of a personality</i>

3
00:00:53,616 --> 00:00:55,326
<i>and a pretty shallow education.</i>

4
00:00:58,329 --> 00:01:00,665
<i>Landing a job is next to impossible…</i>

5
00:01:04,878 --> 00:01:06,004
<i>and to top it all off…</i>

6
00:01:15,597 --> 00:01:17,265
How about another surgery?

7
00:01:18,933 --> 00:01:19,893
Wouldn't that work?

8
00:01:19,976 --> 00:01:21,311
The thing is,

9
00:01:22,103 --> 00:01:25,690
your congestive heart failure
is too advanced.

10
00:01:27,066 --> 00:01:29,694
Your body wouldn't be able to handle it.

11
00:01:33,239 --> 00:01:34,282
So I'm…

12
00:01:36,743 --> 00:01:37,952
really going to die?

13
00:01:45,126 --> 00:01:48,463
<i>A heart that could fail at any moment.</i>

14
00:01:51,799 --> 00:01:54,969
Those who do not believe in God
will be marked by the beast!

15
00:01:55,053 --> 00:01:58,056
And those marked by the beast
will go to hell!

16
00:01:58,139 --> 00:02:00,558
Be saved, everyone!

17
00:02:01,601 --> 00:02:03,394
<i>A life with no escape</i>

18
00:02:04,520 --> 00:02:07,565
<i>that won't change</i>

19
00:02:08,149 --> 00:02:11,653
<i>and has an all too predictable end.</i>

20
00:02:13,613 --> 00:02:14,781
Be saved.

21
00:02:16,783 --> 00:02:18,326
Find salvation.

22
00:02:18,409 --> 00:02:20,245
Find salvation through eternal life.

23
00:02:20,745 --> 00:02:22,247
Don't you wish to be saved?

24
00:02:22,747 --> 00:02:26,459
The apocalypse will happen
on December 31, 1999.

25
00:02:26,542 --> 00:02:28,127
By "the apocalypse,"

26
00:02:29,587 --> 00:02:31,089
do you mean the world will end?

27
00:02:31,172 --> 00:02:32,674
That's right.

28
00:02:32,757 --> 00:02:34,384
But don't you worry.

29
00:02:34,467 --> 00:02:37,679
The blessed will be granted eternal life.

30
00:02:39,430 --> 00:02:42,141
Couldn't it be granted
before Judgment Day?

31
00:02:42,225 --> 00:02:43,434
Sorry?

32
00:02:43,518 --> 00:02:47,021
What about the people who croak
before the apocalypse?

33
00:02:47,105 --> 00:02:51,901
Can't those people be saved in advance?

34
00:02:52,402 --> 00:02:55,530
What, you don't take reservations?

35
00:02:55,613 --> 00:02:58,032
Or maybe move the apocalypse up a little!

36
00:02:58,116 --> 00:03:01,953
Well, there's nothing we can do
about God's will.

37
00:03:02,036 --> 00:03:03,746
What about me, then?

38
00:03:03,830 --> 00:03:05,164
<i>Those who shall be saved…</i>

39
00:03:05,248 --> 00:03:08,293
I want to see the world ending too!

40
00:03:08,376 --> 00:03:11,546
Don't you think it's a raw deal
for me to die without seeing that?

41
00:03:11,629 --> 00:03:13,506
How would I ever rest in peace?

42
00:03:14,924 --> 00:03:15,758
Well?

43
00:03:15,842 --> 00:03:17,510
Have a blessed day.

44
00:03:17,593 --> 00:03:19,929
What, am I asking for too much?

45
00:03:20,013 --> 00:03:22,432
It's not like I'm asking to live forever!

46
00:03:23,182 --> 00:03:28,479
I just want to live long enough to see it!
The end of the world!

47
00:03:28,980 --> 00:03:30,565
I want to see it too!

48
00:03:30,648 --> 00:03:33,192
Show me! I want to see it! Let me see it!

49
00:03:33,276 --> 00:03:35,320
I want to see it!

50
00:03:35,403 --> 00:03:36,821
Let me…

51
00:03:49,459 --> 00:03:52,253
I want to see the entire world…

52
00:03:54,630 --> 00:03:56,174
go up in flames.

53
00:03:58,009 --> 00:03:59,093
How come

54
00:04:00,553 --> 00:04:02,680
I'm not even allowed that?

55
00:04:05,308 --> 00:04:07,935
That's the least I could ask for.

56
00:04:24,452 --> 00:04:26,662
Did you eat a Jaws bar too?

57
00:04:35,046 --> 00:04:35,880
Yeah.

58
00:04:36,589 --> 00:04:37,423
I have now.

59
00:04:52,522 --> 00:04:54,399
Don't cry. Hush.

60
00:04:58,069 --> 00:05:00,571
What if I give you this instead?

61
00:05:03,449 --> 00:05:04,283
Jin-seo!

62
00:05:05,493 --> 00:05:06,953
What are you doing here?

63
00:05:07,453 --> 00:05:10,039
Are you okay?
Mommy has been looking for you.

64
00:05:13,084 --> 00:05:15,044
She's the official trainwreck of Haeseong.

65
00:05:15,128 --> 00:05:17,713
Hey misters,
may you live long, healthy lives.

66
00:05:17,797 --> 00:05:21,008
She's the granddaughter of
the Hearty House owner and a total nutter.

67
00:05:21,092 --> 00:05:22,260
Live long lives, okay?

68
00:05:22,343 --> 00:05:24,178
Best stay away from her, Un-jeong.

69
00:05:24,262 --> 00:05:26,681
-She bites.
-Lucky you, getting to see the apocalypse.

70
00:05:26,764 --> 00:05:28,099
Let's get a move on, people.

71
00:05:28,182 --> 00:05:30,143
-Let's get going.
-How fun!

72
00:05:30,643 --> 00:05:32,854
I swear, this sort of crap is…

73
00:05:35,815 --> 00:05:38,192
What's the point of all this, anyway?

74
00:05:38,693 --> 00:05:42,280
Just go on vacation, everyone! Go travel!

75
00:05:42,822 --> 00:05:44,407
WARNING
THIS IS PRIVATE PROPERTY

76
00:05:44,490 --> 00:05:47,827
TRESPASSING, LITTERING, AND OTHER
ILLEGAL ACTIVITIES ARE PROHIBITED

77
00:05:56,335 --> 00:05:57,336
What's this?

78
00:05:59,005 --> 00:06:00,715
Why, this is perfectly fine.

79
00:06:02,049 --> 00:06:03,468
Do folks have money to burn?

80
00:06:11,225 --> 00:06:13,603
Man, this is really buried deep.

81
00:06:18,733 --> 00:06:21,068
Is someone pulling the darn thing?

82
00:06:38,044 --> 00:06:38,961
What's this?

83
00:08:30,906 --> 00:08:34,577
THE WONDERFOOLS

84
00:08:35,786 --> 00:08:40,416
EPISODE 1
EVERY LIFE COMES WITH A SURPRISE TWIST

85
00:08:42,168 --> 00:08:44,670
I'm pretty sure they're serial murders.

86
00:08:50,134 --> 00:08:54,263
Two weeks ago, Park Yong-sik here
disappeared, and I can't reach him.

87
00:08:54,347 --> 00:08:57,725
Then last week, Kim Bong-pal
also vanished out of the blue.

88
00:08:57,808 --> 00:09:00,394
Maybe you should stop fighting.

89
00:09:00,478 --> 00:09:04,398
No one likes a guy who picks fights
while drunk. I'd cut ties with you too.

90
00:09:04,482 --> 00:09:07,276
I owe Kim Bong-pal 5,000 won.

91
00:09:07,360 --> 00:09:09,779
He'd never cut ties
without getting his money!

92
00:09:11,113 --> 00:09:12,198
Unless he's dead.

93
00:09:12,281 --> 00:09:16,577
Then why don't you file
an official police report?

94
00:09:16,661 --> 00:09:19,455
As if the police would ever listen to me!

95
00:09:20,081 --> 00:09:23,417
Don't you folks say
you listen to the people?

96
00:09:23,501 --> 00:09:25,378
Oh, for God's sake. Where do I--

97
00:09:25,461 --> 00:09:26,671
It's written in the law.

98
00:09:26,754 --> 00:09:30,508
"Article 7, Clause 1. Civil servants
are obliged to serve all citizens…"

99
00:09:35,596 --> 00:09:36,430
Hey, this one.

100
00:09:36,514 --> 00:09:38,516
-This is Kim Na-yeong.
-Stop faking a call.

101
00:09:38,599 --> 00:09:40,768
-Where are you going?
-I don't have a computer.

102
00:09:40,851 --> 00:09:44,021
No, I can't do this.
This is bad. Real bad. Where is he?

103
00:09:45,231 --> 00:09:46,774
Mr. Lee Un-jeong!

104
00:09:49,068 --> 00:09:50,027
This way!

105
00:09:50,111 --> 00:09:51,862
Over here. Right here.

106
00:09:51,946 --> 00:09:52,863
Yes, sir?

107
00:09:52,947 --> 00:09:53,948
Come here.

108
00:09:54,031 --> 00:09:54,865
Right.

109
00:09:56,617 --> 00:09:58,786
You should go. We'll look into it for you.

110
00:10:00,913 --> 00:10:02,123
Why, that…

111
00:10:04,500 --> 00:10:06,085
Oh dear, sorry.

112
00:10:07,044 --> 00:10:08,754
-I'll do it.
-That's okay.

113
00:10:09,380 --> 00:10:12,633
Isn't it about time
for your rite of passage?

114
00:10:13,342 --> 00:10:15,219
He's a regular at our complaints office.

115
00:10:21,642 --> 00:10:23,144
Are you accusing me of lying?

116
00:10:23,644 --> 00:10:26,063
The carp really was
as tall as I am sitting down.

117
00:10:26,147 --> 00:10:29,066
I have a long torso, so seated,
I'm at least 120 centimeters tall!

118
00:10:29,150 --> 00:10:31,652
It was clearly genetically modified!

119
00:10:31,736 --> 00:10:34,697
Someone's been dumping phenol
into the water!

120
00:10:34,780 --> 00:10:38,075
You know <i>V</i>, right?
The show about aliens who eat rats!

121
00:10:38,159 --> 00:10:41,495
It blinked its eyelids sideways,
just like the aliens on that show!

122
00:10:41,579 --> 00:10:43,414
I'm telling you, it's phenol.

123
00:10:43,497 --> 00:10:46,792
Why won't you take my word for it
and go there for an inspection?

124
00:10:46,876 --> 00:10:50,463
Either there's a corpse rotting
somewhere in that reservoir,

125
00:10:50,546 --> 00:10:51,589
or it's phenol!

126
00:10:52,089 --> 00:10:53,841
Just go out there and check!

127
00:10:54,592 --> 00:10:56,552
You have to deal with him

128
00:10:56,635 --> 00:10:58,971
to become a true complaint troubleshooter.

129
00:10:59,054 --> 00:11:02,308
Oddly enough, my stomach's acting up,
so I need the bathroom.

130
00:11:02,391 --> 00:11:03,392
But, sir…

131
00:11:07,938 --> 00:11:09,190
Look at this, will you?

132
00:11:09,273 --> 00:11:12,318
It's a total garbage dump, you know?
You see that?

133
00:11:12,401 --> 00:11:13,611
-Now--
-One moment, sir.

134
00:11:19,366 --> 00:11:20,367
Yes, here.

135
00:11:21,619 --> 00:11:25,039
Our records show
that we already did an inspection

136
00:11:25,122 --> 00:11:27,500
and installed signs
prohibiting illegal dumping.

137
00:11:28,501 --> 00:11:29,460
This thing?

138
00:11:29,543 --> 00:11:31,170
This isn't enough!

139
00:11:31,253 --> 00:11:34,465
Who'd be afraid of a measly sign
that has no legal effect?

140
00:11:34,548 --> 00:11:35,800
-Look.
-One moment, sir.

141
00:11:44,725 --> 00:11:48,312
This land is private property,
so there really isn't anything we can…

142
00:11:49,230 --> 00:11:54,026
Without the owner's consent,
our hands are pretty much tied, sir.

143
00:11:58,531 --> 00:11:59,907
Do my words carry no weight

144
00:11:59,990 --> 00:12:02,952
because I grab a ticket
and patiently wait my turn to see you?

145
00:12:03,661 --> 00:12:05,287
Mr. Lee Un-jeong? Okay.

146
00:12:05,371 --> 00:12:09,875
Should I just go straight to Manager Kim
and get you into trouble?

147
00:12:10,376 --> 00:12:13,879
Or should I go upstairs right now
and take this up with Director Lee?

148
00:12:14,463 --> 00:12:15,297
Well?

149
00:12:15,798 --> 00:12:17,299
Unbelievable.

150
00:12:18,008 --> 00:12:18,843
Honestly!

151
00:12:20,845 --> 00:12:21,971
At Haeseong City Hall,

152
00:12:22,054 --> 00:12:25,307
we have eleven Manager Kims
and four Director Lees.

153
00:12:25,891 --> 00:12:29,019
Which one would you like to speak to, sir?

154
00:12:29,103 --> 00:12:30,271
What's that?

155
00:12:33,649 --> 00:12:37,444
Why, you're one hell of an oddball,
aren't you?

156
00:12:51,750 --> 00:12:52,585
Next, please!

157
00:12:52,668 --> 00:12:54,295
"Next, please"?

158
00:13:03,888 --> 00:13:05,347
You should watch out.

159
00:13:07,683 --> 00:13:11,687
From here, this looks like a quiet
and peaceful rural town, doesn't it?

160
00:13:13,689 --> 00:13:15,024
But it isn't.

161
00:13:15,524 --> 00:13:17,693
If you take a closer look,

162
00:13:18,360 --> 00:13:20,988
there's no place more troubled than this.

163
00:13:27,161 --> 00:13:29,622
People keep disappearing.

164
00:13:31,540 --> 00:13:33,459
Just like 20 years ago.

165
00:13:39,882 --> 00:13:41,216
Last time,

166
00:13:42,843 --> 00:13:47,973
dozens of people,
children and adults alike, went missing.

167
00:13:51,518 --> 00:13:52,978
You'd better be careful.

168
00:13:53,562 --> 00:13:57,232
I figured you wouldn't know,
since you're not from around here.

169
00:14:00,027 --> 00:14:00,945
Yes, sir.

170
00:14:02,279 --> 00:14:03,989
I saw it all.

171
00:14:05,282 --> 00:14:08,035
What happened 20 years ago.

172
00:14:47,533 --> 00:14:48,951
Be saved, sir.

173
00:14:51,620 --> 00:14:55,040
Don't you people have something
better to do? You're such a pain!

174
00:14:56,375 --> 00:14:57,626
Go away!

175
00:15:00,337 --> 00:15:01,338
I said go away!

176
00:15:09,096 --> 00:15:11,140
What is this?

177
00:15:11,223 --> 00:15:14,852
What are you trying to pull?

178
00:15:28,949 --> 00:15:30,200
Believe,

179
00:15:31,618 --> 00:15:33,412
and you shall be saved.

180
00:15:39,626 --> 00:15:40,711
Send me on a trip.

181
00:15:42,379 --> 00:15:43,797
Oh, for crying out loud.

182
00:15:45,716 --> 00:15:47,426
I said I'm going on a trip.

183
00:15:47,509 --> 00:15:48,886
Give me some money!

184
00:15:49,386 --> 00:15:50,220
No.

185
00:15:50,304 --> 00:15:52,097
-Why not?
-Do you really have to ask?

186
00:15:52,806 --> 00:15:55,392
What, are you gonna take your cash
to the afterlife?

187
00:15:55,476 --> 00:15:58,937
You donate hundreds of millions to others,
so why won't you donate to me?

188
00:15:59,021 --> 00:16:01,231
That'd be a waste of money,
not a donation.

189
00:16:02,107 --> 00:16:06,278
Money is only money when you know
how to spend it. Otherwise, it's poison.

190
00:16:06,361 --> 00:16:09,656
We won't know until I've tried spending,
so just give me some!

191
00:16:09,740 --> 00:16:11,450
Let me at least splurge before I die.

192
00:16:12,701 --> 00:16:15,537
Don't you know that death talk
is forbidden in our house?

193
00:16:20,876 --> 00:16:23,420
What is it? Did the doctor say something?

194
00:16:26,298 --> 00:16:29,134
I just mean, what do I have to live for?

195
00:16:29,218 --> 00:16:32,012
I can't go anywhere or do whatever I want!

196
00:16:32,096 --> 00:16:34,098
If you're so unhappy,
then you be my grandma.

197
00:16:35,891 --> 00:16:39,269
Unless you want your pay docked,
cut the crap and go peel some onions.

198
00:16:40,896 --> 00:16:43,899
And don't forget
to take your meds on time, okay?

199
00:16:43,982 --> 00:16:46,568
Do you even know how hard it is
to be your granddaughter?

200
00:16:46,652 --> 00:16:49,947
I don't know about that, but I bet
being your grandma is even harder.

201
00:16:54,993 --> 00:16:58,372
<i>As expected,</i>
<i>Grandma won't give me any money.</i>

202
00:17:29,945 --> 00:17:31,029
KILIMANJARO
AURORA

203
00:17:38,162 --> 00:17:40,747
<i>Okay, let's do it.</i>

204
00:17:41,248 --> 00:17:45,544
<i>I'm gonna visit</i>
<i>at least one place before I die.</i>

205
00:18:00,392 --> 00:18:01,226
Going somewhere?

206
00:18:01,310 --> 00:18:03,312
Yeah, I am. On a trip.

207
00:18:04,688 --> 00:18:07,316
-Your grandma let you?
-Do you think she would?

208
00:18:07,399 --> 00:18:08,442
But what about money?

209
00:18:08,525 --> 00:18:09,860
You'll lend me some.

210
00:18:09,943 --> 00:18:11,153
Right… What?

211
00:18:11,653 --> 00:18:13,197
I can't. I don't have any.

212
00:18:13,280 --> 00:18:15,532
What? Why don't you have any money?

213
00:18:15,616 --> 00:18:17,993
My roof kept leaking.

214
00:18:18,076 --> 00:18:20,287
I had to cash out my savings to fix it.

215
00:18:20,370 --> 00:18:23,498
You're a tenant.
Shouldn't your landlord deal with repairs?

216
00:18:23,582 --> 00:18:25,709
He said he'd fix it next month.

217
00:18:25,792 --> 00:18:29,546
Then you should've waited a month.
Why would you pay? Are you stupid?

218
00:18:29,630 --> 00:18:32,925
Hey, have you ever had to use an umbrella
inside your own home?

219
00:18:33,842 --> 00:18:38,138
You sure live up to your name,
Sappiest Sap of Haeseong.

220
00:18:39,640 --> 00:18:40,933
Anyway, I'm broke.

221
00:18:41,850 --> 00:18:44,228
Anyway, I'm going on a trip.

222
00:18:44,311 --> 00:18:45,687
How exactly?

223
00:18:46,605 --> 00:18:50,025
I see. You have some assets
since you're an heiress and all?

224
00:18:50,609 --> 00:18:52,444
You really are clueless, aren't you?

225
00:18:52,527 --> 00:18:55,155
You have to inherit something
to be an heiress.

226
00:18:55,239 --> 00:18:57,407
-But--
-Who's out there? Eunie?

227
00:18:57,491 --> 00:18:59,201
Did you take your meds?

228
00:19:00,994 --> 00:19:03,664
Which one of us
do you think will live longer?

229
00:19:03,747 --> 00:19:05,666
Take your darn meds!

230
00:19:05,749 --> 00:19:07,501
I already did!

231
00:19:09,711 --> 00:19:11,213
I bet she'll live to 120.

232
00:19:13,215 --> 00:19:14,383
See ya, Sap.

233
00:19:15,008 --> 00:19:15,842
Hey!

234
00:19:16,343 --> 00:19:18,470
How are you gonna travel
without any money?

235
00:19:19,346 --> 00:19:20,514
Don't worry.

236
00:19:21,014 --> 00:19:22,391
This is top secret,

237
00:19:24,184 --> 00:19:27,521
but tomorrow,
I'm due to be 50 million won richer.

238
00:19:34,611 --> 00:19:37,239
So when will it be dealt with?

239
00:19:37,322 --> 00:19:39,241
You know how civil servants are.

240
00:19:40,200 --> 00:19:41,201
A bunch of slowpokes.

241
00:19:42,411 --> 00:19:45,789
I'll try to handle things myself
as swiftly as possible.

242
00:19:46,290 --> 00:19:47,582
But more importantly…

243
00:19:50,043 --> 00:19:52,462
about my mom's 70th birthday trip.

244
00:19:53,547 --> 00:19:55,799
You know we get westerlies
in the summer, right?

245
00:19:56,925 --> 00:19:59,177
Just thinking about how much I suffered

246
00:19:59,261 --> 00:20:01,722
because of the stench
since we had that heavy rain…

247
00:20:02,681 --> 00:20:04,850
-Sales have plummeted too.
-Right.

248
00:20:04,933 --> 00:20:08,103
Who'd want to come
to a flower shop that stinks of rot?

249
00:20:08,186 --> 00:20:10,480
Right, I'll get it dealt with quickly.

250
00:20:12,190 --> 00:20:16,153
Well, once that's done,
my mom's 70th birthday trip…

251
00:20:16,653 --> 00:20:18,530
Why do you keep bringing that up?

252
00:20:18,613 --> 00:20:20,532
I thought we were done talking about it.

253
00:20:20,615 --> 00:20:23,076
You only turn 70 once in your life.

254
00:20:23,577 --> 00:20:25,829
She's never been on a plane before.

255
00:20:25,912 --> 00:20:28,874
Just take her
to the Hawaii resort in Bugok.

256
00:20:28,957 --> 00:20:31,293
The good son act is over in a flash,

257
00:20:31,376 --> 00:20:33,628
but credit card debt lasts a lifetime.

258
00:20:34,254 --> 00:20:35,088
Still--

259
00:20:35,172 --> 00:20:36,298
Yikes, a bug!

260
00:20:38,008 --> 00:20:39,426
Why won't it get off? Why?

261
00:20:39,509 --> 00:20:41,928
Go away! Get off! Oh, I'm so sick of you!

262
00:20:42,012 --> 00:20:44,473
Die, damn it! Die!

263
00:20:44,973 --> 00:20:46,224
Die!

264
00:20:48,018 --> 00:20:51,313
Everything's ready.
Enjoy lunch, Ms. Moon Mi-hui.

265
00:20:54,775 --> 00:20:55,859
It looks pretty dead…

266
00:21:01,698 --> 00:21:03,325
HAESEONG GIRLS' MIDDLE SCHOOL

267
00:21:03,408 --> 00:21:04,534
Seo-yeong, here.

268
00:21:04,618 --> 00:21:06,828
Hey, I'm here. Over here!

269
00:21:09,289 --> 00:21:10,165
Hello?

270
00:21:10,248 --> 00:21:12,417
Hi, Mom. Yeah.

271
00:21:13,502 --> 00:21:14,628
Yes.

272
00:21:15,670 --> 00:21:19,132
Yes, just wait a little longer.
You said it's three months away.

273
00:21:19,758 --> 00:21:20,592
Cheong!

274
00:21:29,017 --> 00:21:29,851
Okay, Mom.

275
00:21:31,269 --> 00:21:32,437
Yes.

276
00:21:32,521 --> 00:21:34,189
Oh, of course.

277
00:21:34,689 --> 00:21:36,316
I'll send you to Hawaii.

278
00:21:37,192 --> 00:21:38,193
Don't you worry.

279
00:21:38,693 --> 00:21:40,570
You know how capable your son is--

280
00:21:45,409 --> 00:21:47,702
Goodness, these shoes…

281
00:21:47,786 --> 00:21:48,787
Mom?

282
00:21:49,287 --> 00:21:50,956
I gotta go. I'll call you later.

283
00:21:51,790 --> 00:21:52,624
Bye.

284
00:21:54,292 --> 00:21:55,836
-Bo-ra, let's go together.
-Sure.

285
00:21:56,420 --> 00:21:58,922
-Want to go get <i>tteokbokki</i>?
-That sounds great.

286
00:21:59,005 --> 00:22:00,590
-Okay!
-Should we skip cram school?

287
00:22:00,674 --> 00:22:02,426
Sweet, sounds good!

288
00:22:02,509 --> 00:22:03,343
Let's go.

289
00:22:04,052 --> 00:22:05,554
My shoes are soaked.

290
00:22:14,146 --> 00:22:16,148
Wow, 50 million won.

291
00:22:16,857 --> 00:22:18,567
I'm so jealous.

292
00:22:35,167 --> 00:22:37,335
There's nothing to steal.
Why lock the door?

293
00:22:37,419 --> 00:22:39,379
It's to keep things out.

294
00:22:39,880 --> 00:22:41,840
Like bugs, cats…

295
00:22:43,091 --> 00:22:43,967
Especially you.

296
00:22:49,890 --> 00:22:52,601
Hey, why'd you shut the door in my face?

297
00:22:53,310 --> 00:22:54,936
Oh no!

298
00:23:00,567 --> 00:23:02,360
Hey, there.

299
00:23:05,739 --> 00:23:07,324
Didn't you say you got it fixed?

300
00:23:08,950 --> 00:23:10,327
I did.

301
00:23:11,912 --> 00:23:14,831
I paid a lot of money for it too.

302
00:23:14,915 --> 00:23:16,917
Are you laughing or crying?

303
00:24:51,052 --> 00:24:52,971
Chae-ni, are you going somewhere?

304
00:24:53,054 --> 00:24:54,806
And your grandma actually let you?

305
00:24:54,889 --> 00:24:56,808
Well, Chae-ni, you sure are lucky.

306
00:24:56,891 --> 00:24:59,728
-What's gotten into the Hearty House lady?
-Exactly.

307
00:24:59,811 --> 00:25:02,188
Chae-ni, aren't you lucky?
Have a great trip!

308
00:25:02,272 --> 00:25:04,774
-Is Chae-ni going somewhere?
-I think she's traveling.

309
00:25:05,275 --> 00:25:08,320
Always best to travel
while your knees are still good!

310
00:25:39,643 --> 00:25:40,644
What?

311
00:25:41,561 --> 00:25:42,771
What the heck?

312
00:25:45,732 --> 00:25:46,900
Damn it.

313
00:25:55,283 --> 00:25:56,493
It's Mr. Kim's.

314
00:25:57,619 --> 00:25:59,621
Where did he go without his cart?

315
00:26:00,955 --> 00:26:02,415
I'll bring it back soon.

316
00:26:19,391 --> 00:26:21,685
Isn't this Mr. Kim Bong-pal's cart?

317
00:26:23,603 --> 00:26:24,437
Who are you?

318
00:26:26,773 --> 00:26:28,608
Are you the new supermarket manager?

319
00:26:32,737 --> 00:26:33,780
Fine, take it.

320
00:26:33,863 --> 00:26:35,573
Take it. It's all yours.

321
00:26:56,970 --> 00:26:59,389
<i>I'm pretty sure they're serial murders.</i>

322
00:27:00,390 --> 00:27:02,559
<i>She's the official trainwreck of Haeseong.</i>

323
00:27:02,642 --> 00:27:03,852
<i>Best stay away from her.</i>

324
00:27:03,935 --> 00:27:05,478
<i>You'd better be careful.</i>

325
00:27:05,562 --> 00:27:07,731
People keep disappearing.

326
00:27:11,651 --> 00:27:12,861
What are you doing?

327
00:27:14,028 --> 00:27:15,363
That's a pretty big suitcase.

328
00:27:16,072 --> 00:27:17,574
What's it to you?

329
00:27:19,909 --> 00:27:21,911
Where is Mr. Kim Bong-pal?

330
00:27:23,037 --> 00:27:24,372
How would I know?

331
00:27:25,457 --> 00:27:27,751
May I check your suitcase?

332
00:27:27,834 --> 00:27:29,043
What do you have in here?

333
00:27:29,127 --> 00:27:32,881
Whatever I wanted to put in there!
What do you want with my suitcase?

334
00:27:35,550 --> 00:27:36,384
What the…

335
00:27:38,219 --> 00:27:39,095
What the heck?

336
00:27:40,889 --> 00:27:42,223
Let go!

337
00:28:36,152 --> 00:28:37,362
I'll…

338
00:28:49,249 --> 00:28:50,500
I think there's been a--

339
00:29:06,724 --> 00:29:07,600
Hello?

340
00:29:08,101 --> 00:29:10,645
<i>Being out in the rain</i>
<i>won't do you any good.</i>

341
00:29:10,728 --> 00:29:12,063
<i>Where'd you go?</i>

342
00:29:12,647 --> 00:29:13,648
I just

343
00:29:14,357 --> 00:29:16,067
had to take care of something.

344
00:29:16,150 --> 00:29:17,193
<i>Take care of what?</i>

345
00:29:17,694 --> 00:29:20,572
<i>What could you possibly have</i>
<i>to take care of in the rain?</i>

346
00:29:21,406 --> 00:29:22,657
<i>Where are you?</i>

347
00:29:23,700 --> 00:29:24,659
<i>Hey, say…</i>

348
00:29:24,742 --> 00:29:25,827
<i>Hello?</i>

349
00:29:27,120 --> 00:29:27,954
<i>Hello?</i>

350
00:29:28,454 --> 00:29:29,581
<i>-Hello?</i>
-Grandma, hold on.

351
00:29:37,130 --> 00:29:38,214
Your contact info.

352
00:29:50,393 --> 00:29:52,228
JUNIOR OFFICIAL LEE UN-JEONG

353
00:29:54,022 --> 00:29:55,523
Haeseong City Hall Complaints?

354
00:29:55,607 --> 00:29:57,025
<i>Haeseong City Hall Complaints?</i>

355
00:29:57,108 --> 00:29:59,611
<i>Why? Did someone</i>
<i>file a complaint against you?</i>

356
00:29:59,694 --> 00:30:01,404
<i>What did you do this time?</i>

357
00:30:01,487 --> 00:30:04,240
My lawyer will be in touch, so hang tight.

358
00:30:04,741 --> 00:30:06,784
Dry cleaning money won't cut it.

359
00:30:07,744 --> 00:30:08,578
Okay.

360
00:30:13,666 --> 00:30:14,542
Goodbye, then.

361
00:30:22,842 --> 00:30:25,637
It's nothing, Grandma. But why'd you call?

362
00:30:25,720 --> 00:30:27,305
Why do you think?

363
00:30:27,388 --> 00:30:29,432
What if you catch a cold? Hurry home.

364
00:30:30,224 --> 00:30:33,061
<i>I told you not to go out</i>
<i>when the weather changes.</i>

365
00:30:34,520 --> 00:30:35,813
Grandma.

366
00:30:38,024 --> 00:30:40,401
Can't you just let me go on a trip?

367
00:30:42,028 --> 00:30:43,821
There you go again with that nonsense.

368
00:30:45,740 --> 00:30:48,576
How could you travel in your condition?

369
00:30:50,036 --> 00:30:54,916
Is living a <i>long </i>life
all that you want for me?

370
00:30:55,500 --> 00:30:58,544
Incapable of doing anything,
just wasting away?

371
00:31:00,213 --> 00:31:02,298
<i>Doesn't it frustrate you</i>
<i>to see me like this?</i>

372
00:31:02,382 --> 00:31:04,300
Aren't you embarrassed
to face the neighbors?

373
00:31:05,426 --> 00:31:06,427
I'm not.

374
00:31:07,637 --> 00:31:08,930
Why would I be embarrassed?

375
00:31:10,390 --> 00:31:11,975
I'm just waiting.

376
00:31:13,476 --> 00:31:16,312
<i>What, you think you were healthy as a kid?</i>

377
00:31:17,897 --> 00:31:19,065
But still,

378
00:31:20,233 --> 00:31:21,567
you were ever so kind,

379
00:31:22,068 --> 00:31:23,361
well-mannered,

380
00:31:24,070 --> 00:31:25,488
and always gave your best.

381
00:31:27,657 --> 00:31:29,117
You were such a darling.

382
00:31:30,076 --> 00:31:33,579
You weren't good at anything,
but you were still such a darling.

383
00:31:34,205 --> 00:31:36,290
Because you powered through and lived on.

384
00:31:39,043 --> 00:31:44,007
I'm waiting for the day when that darling
Eun Chae-ni hiding deep inside of you

385
00:31:45,758 --> 00:31:47,802
crawls her way out.

386
00:31:52,849 --> 00:31:54,017
Well, don't.

387
00:31:54,726 --> 00:31:56,227
She died a long time ago.

388
00:31:56,310 --> 00:31:58,062
Eunie, you really…

389
00:31:58,563 --> 00:32:00,898
I told you not to talk about dying.

390
00:32:01,566 --> 00:32:03,943
I told you
that's off-limits in this house!

391
00:32:06,154 --> 00:32:07,572
<i>The thing is, Grandma,</i>

392
00:32:08,740 --> 00:32:10,283
<i>I really am going to die.</i>

393
00:32:23,838 --> 00:32:27,508
<i>But I never imagined I'd die like this.</i>

394
00:32:30,845 --> 00:32:35,224
<i>Without you by my side</i>
<i>and in front of these guys, no less.</i>

395
00:32:45,860 --> 00:32:47,570
<i>Now, </i>this <i>is a plot twist.</i>

396
00:32:47,653 --> 00:32:51,783
So you wasted two million
on waterproof paint for the roof?

397
00:32:51,866 --> 00:32:53,284
Shame on you.

398
00:32:53,367 --> 00:32:55,495
I knew you weren't just any old sap.

399
00:32:55,578 --> 00:32:58,790
You deserve to be called
the sappiest of all saps.

400
00:33:03,586 --> 00:33:06,297
I wish money would just fall
from the sky--

401
00:33:09,509 --> 00:33:11,219
If only there were cash lying around.

402
00:33:12,095 --> 00:33:13,554
Why's it taking so long to boil?

403
00:33:15,223 --> 00:33:18,726
Nothing in life goes my goddamn way.

404
00:33:19,310 --> 00:33:21,813
Yet some people are going on vacation
with 50 million.

405
00:33:21,896 --> 00:33:23,523
Who is?

406
00:33:23,606 --> 00:33:26,150
Who has 50 million to blow on a vacation?

407
00:33:26,234 --> 00:33:29,028
Who else would I know
who has that much money?

408
00:33:29,112 --> 00:33:31,614
There's no way
the Hearty House owner would travel.

409
00:33:33,032 --> 00:33:36,160
Her granddaughter?
Eun Chae-ni, Lady Trainwreck?

410
00:33:40,331 --> 00:33:41,165
Begone!

411
00:33:42,500 --> 00:33:44,252
Did you just call me a trainwreck?

412
00:33:45,002 --> 00:33:48,339
Yeah. What's wrong with calling
a trainwreck a trainwreck?

413
00:33:49,006 --> 00:33:49,841
Touché.

414
00:33:50,967 --> 00:33:52,552
You're right, Mr. Royal Nightmare.

415
00:33:52,635 --> 00:33:53,553
What, Nightmare?

416
00:33:53,636 --> 00:33:55,555
Watch what you call your elders, you brat.

417
00:33:55,638 --> 00:33:58,015
What's wrong with calling
a nightmare a nightmare?

418
00:33:58,599 --> 00:34:00,143
-Why, you little brat--
-Stop.

419
00:34:00,226 --> 00:34:01,811
Come on, Chae-ni.

420
00:34:01,894 --> 00:34:04,105
Mr. Son, you too.
Easy with that stink eye.

421
00:34:04,188 --> 00:34:06,649
Stay out of this, Sappy Sap of Haeseong.

422
00:34:06,732 --> 00:34:08,442
Yeah, butt out, Sappy Sap.

423
00:34:08,526 --> 00:34:10,903
Hey, I asked you not to call me that.

424
00:34:10,987 --> 00:34:13,114
It makes me feel left out.

425
00:34:13,197 --> 00:34:15,658
You guys are the only ones
who get cool nicknames.

426
00:34:16,242 --> 00:34:18,661
Can't you give me a cool nickname
like "King Sap"?

427
00:34:18,744 --> 00:34:21,539
King Sap sounds like
a pretty powerful sap, at least.

428
00:34:21,622 --> 00:34:23,082
You think anyone can be a royal?

429
00:34:23,166 --> 00:34:24,292
Of course not.

430
00:34:24,375 --> 00:34:27,545
You need to build up a bad rep for years,
constantly pick fights,

431
00:34:27,628 --> 00:34:29,714
and have the tenacity and perseverance

432
00:34:29,797 --> 00:34:33,259
to not give a hoot about others
in order to be crowned a royal.

433
00:34:33,843 --> 00:34:34,886
Give me a break.

434
00:34:34,969 --> 00:34:37,263
I'd expect no less
from Haeseong's Royal Nightmare.

435
00:34:37,847 --> 00:34:39,515
Someone's brimming with pride.

436
00:34:39,599 --> 00:34:42,268
I heard you were going on
a 50-million-won trip,

437
00:34:42,351 --> 00:34:44,687
but I guess you sent your manners
on the road early.

438
00:34:44,770 --> 00:34:47,815
Did your manners
take your sense of respect with them?

439
00:34:47,899 --> 00:34:49,817
Too bad. Will you even be able to go?

440
00:34:49,901 --> 00:34:53,154
How could you leave Haeseong
when everyone knows your grandma?

441
00:34:53,237 --> 00:34:56,324
Man, I almost want to rat you out.

442
00:34:57,366 --> 00:34:58,409
That's why

443
00:34:59,619 --> 00:35:01,746
the Royal Nightmare and Sappy Sap

444
00:35:02,663 --> 00:35:03,497
need to help me.

445
00:35:03,581 --> 00:35:06,667
You think I'd help a kid
who calls her elder a "nightmare"?

446
00:35:06,751 --> 00:35:09,253
I'll compensate you generously.
Five million each.

447
00:35:09,337 --> 00:35:12,006
What should we do first, m'lady?

448
00:35:13,174 --> 00:35:15,092
First, I should bring in my luggage.

449
00:35:15,176 --> 00:35:17,386
Please, leave it to me,
your humble servant.

450
00:35:17,887 --> 00:35:19,472
We're already on it, ma'am.

451
00:35:23,017 --> 00:35:25,311
<i>What did I possibly do that was so wrong?</i>

452
00:35:26,395 --> 00:35:28,231
<i>Where did it all go south?</i>

453
00:35:29,982 --> 00:35:32,818
I forgot that the world
is disgustingly unfair.

454
00:35:32,902 --> 00:35:36,656
Right. They say worrying about an heiress
is the greatest waste of time.

455
00:35:42,536 --> 00:35:44,789
<i>Did I dig my own grave?</i>

456
00:35:49,168 --> 00:35:51,963
The people downstairs complained
about the noise again.

457
00:35:52,046 --> 00:35:53,839
What are you up to every night?

458
00:35:54,757 --> 00:35:56,342
Didn't you say you lived alone?

459
00:35:56,884 --> 00:35:59,553
Why are you thumping away
every night by yourself?

460
00:36:00,137 --> 00:36:02,223
I'm sorry. I'll be more careful.

461
00:36:02,306 --> 00:36:04,684
I told you it's an old building
with thin walls.

462
00:36:04,767 --> 00:36:06,477
Please be more mindful.

463
00:37:02,867 --> 00:37:04,577
ILLEGAL DUMPING IN HAEDEUL-RI HILL

464
00:37:04,660 --> 00:37:06,120
COMPLAINT REPORT

465
00:37:30,978 --> 00:37:31,812
Yes?

466
00:37:36,567 --> 00:37:39,028
I told you I'd be the one to contact you.

467
00:37:42,448 --> 00:37:44,658
You don't have to keep checking up on me.

468
00:37:45,326 --> 00:37:46,660
It's being dealt with.

469
00:38:27,868 --> 00:38:29,453
NUMBER 2415
STATUS: DORMANT

470
00:38:38,170 --> 00:38:39,755
HA WON-DO

471
00:38:43,008 --> 00:38:44,635
CHOI YEONG-JUN

472
00:38:46,512 --> 00:38:49,014
DR. HA WON-DO WINS GERMANY'S
SCIENTIST OF THE YEAR AWARD

473
00:38:49,098 --> 00:38:51,058
CLAIMED TO SAVE HUMANITY, ONLY LEFT SCARS

474
00:38:51,142 --> 00:38:52,643
EXPLOSION AT ORPHANAGE

475
00:38:54,603 --> 00:38:55,771
POLITICIAN CONDEMNS DR. HA

476
00:38:55,855 --> 00:38:57,481
IMMORAL BIOLOGICAL EXPERIMENTS

477
00:38:57,565 --> 00:38:59,316
THE SWEET HOME WELFARE CENTER TRAGEDY

478
00:39:08,242 --> 00:39:12,538
UNVEILING THE HORRIFYING TRUTH
HAWONDO LAB'S SECURITY GUARD TELLS ALL

479
00:40:08,427 --> 00:40:10,471
APOCALYPSE ON DECEMBER 31ST
SEEK SALVATION

480
00:40:12,932 --> 00:40:14,475
CHURCH OF ETERNAL SALVATION

481
00:40:14,558 --> 00:40:17,269
13 HAEDEUL-RI, HAEJEON-EUP, HAESEONG-SI

482
00:41:09,154 --> 00:41:10,030
What…

483
00:41:23,669 --> 00:41:24,712
What's that?

484
00:41:37,891 --> 00:41:39,351
Kim Bong-pal?

485
00:41:40,394 --> 00:41:41,395
<i>In what ways</i>

486
00:41:42,313 --> 00:41:43,981
<i>can money change a person,</i>

487
00:41:44,064 --> 00:41:46,609
<i>and how far can it transform them?</i>

488
00:41:57,620 --> 00:41:58,996
Grandma.

489
00:42:00,497 --> 00:42:01,832
If you just pay them,

490
00:42:03,042 --> 00:42:04,752
I think this'll all be over soon.

491
00:42:07,046 --> 00:42:07,880
All they want

492
00:42:09,715 --> 00:42:10,883
is five big ones.

493
00:42:13,469 --> 00:42:14,595
Five.

494
00:42:17,306 --> 00:42:18,474
<i>If you just pay them…</i>

495
00:42:19,475 --> 00:42:21,518
Is it really okay for us to do this?

496
00:42:22,061 --> 00:42:25,981
Do I look like I'm enjoying this?
Aren't you tired of being called a sap?

497
00:42:28,192 --> 00:42:31,195
Just shut it,
and let's get this over with.

498
00:42:33,489 --> 00:42:34,323
Hey.

499
00:42:38,952 --> 00:42:39,787
<i>Oh no.</i>

500
00:42:41,872 --> 00:42:42,790
Hey…

501
00:42:42,873 --> 00:42:44,291
<i>It's beating too fast.</i>

502
00:42:49,755 --> 00:42:50,756
Why did you do that?

503
00:42:50,839 --> 00:42:51,674
<i>I</i>

504
00:42:53,258 --> 00:42:56,553
<i>really wanted to climb Kilimanjaro.</i>

505
00:42:57,054 --> 00:42:58,764
<i>Or at least see the northern lights.</i>

506
00:43:19,118 --> 00:43:21,286
Grandma…

507
00:43:38,345 --> 00:43:41,515
Hey, I think we can do better.
Let's do one more take.

508
00:43:42,307 --> 00:43:44,727
Okay, three, two…

509
00:43:45,227 --> 00:43:46,061
Action.

510
00:43:57,489 --> 00:43:58,323
Chae-ni.

511
00:43:59,700 --> 00:44:00,784
Chae-ni?

512
00:44:00,868 --> 00:44:02,077
What's wrong with her?

513
00:44:02,578 --> 00:44:03,495
Chae-ni.

514
00:44:28,896 --> 00:44:29,730
Delete that.

515
00:44:29,813 --> 00:44:31,273
What? Why?

516
00:44:31,356 --> 00:44:32,524
Delete it.

517
00:44:47,664 --> 00:44:50,334
What is it?

518
00:44:51,043 --> 00:44:52,920
What's wrong with Chae-ni?

519
00:44:53,545 --> 00:44:55,547
And what's wrong with you?

520
00:44:56,340 --> 00:44:57,257
Chae-ni…

521
00:45:00,093 --> 00:45:01,428
is dead.

522
00:45:10,020 --> 00:45:11,897
INCOMING CALL

523
00:45:15,692 --> 00:45:19,988
<i>At 9:27 p.m.</i>
<i>on a certain day and month in 1999,</i>

524
00:45:21,240 --> 00:45:22,533
<i>ridiculous as it is,</i>

525
00:45:23,116 --> 00:45:24,284
<i>I really</i>

526
00:45:26,078 --> 00:45:27,704
<i>died just like this.</i>

527
00:45:29,206 --> 00:45:32,042
She better not be off somewhere
causing trouble again.

528
00:45:33,418 --> 00:45:37,506
Thanks to you, Eunie,
my life is so full of thrills.

529
00:45:39,967 --> 00:45:41,552
PRIVATE INVESTIGATOR, GU JUN-MO

530
00:45:50,227 --> 00:45:52,521
COLD CASES

531
00:45:52,604 --> 00:45:54,523
URBAN LEGENDS OF HAESEONG

532
00:46:00,821 --> 00:46:02,197
Yes, this is Gu Jun-mo.

533
00:46:02,281 --> 00:46:05,409
Hey, Jun-mo. I need you to do me a favor.

534
00:46:07,244 --> 00:46:08,245
What is it?

535
00:46:08,745 --> 00:46:10,372
Is Eun Chae-ni not answering again?

536
00:46:10,455 --> 00:46:13,542
Since you know, I'll just get to it.
Go ahead and track her.

537
00:46:13,625 --> 00:46:17,045
Why bother paying for that again?
She'll come home when it's time.

538
00:46:17,129 --> 00:46:18,255
Tell me about it.

539
00:46:18,755 --> 00:46:21,592
You could have done it for free
if you were still a cop.

540
00:46:21,675 --> 00:46:23,093
Why quit and make me pay?

541
00:46:23,176 --> 00:46:25,220
I'll look into it right away, ma'am.

542
00:46:37,065 --> 00:46:40,527
Chae-ni, I'm sorry. It's all my fault.

543
00:46:41,194 --> 00:46:44,615
Don't die. Please don't die.

544
00:46:51,747 --> 00:46:52,873
I can't believe this.

545
00:46:53,373 --> 00:46:54,750
How is this possible?

546
00:46:55,459 --> 00:46:58,670
We didn't even lay a finger on her,
so how could she just die?

547
00:46:59,880 --> 00:47:01,423
Who's going to believe this?

548
00:47:01,924 --> 00:47:03,175
And on top of that,

549
00:47:04,885 --> 00:47:06,637
we're her kidnappers right now.

550
00:47:11,224 --> 00:47:14,603
Mr. Son, what are you doing?
I told you to call an ambulance!

551
00:47:16,104 --> 00:47:17,189
It's too late.

552
00:47:17,272 --> 00:47:21,234
Just call them already.
At this rate, we'll really lose Chae-ni!

553
00:47:21,318 --> 00:47:23,904
She's already dead!

554
00:47:24,404 --> 00:47:25,614
Her pupils are…

555
00:47:26,114 --> 00:47:29,993
Her pupils are dilated.

556
00:47:36,333 --> 00:47:38,669
Poor Chae-ni.

557
00:47:39,544 --> 00:47:41,463
What about her poor grandma?

558
00:47:42,214 --> 00:47:44,132
And what about us?

559
00:47:52,182 --> 00:47:54,559
-For now, we hide her.
-What?

560
00:47:55,310 --> 00:47:59,356
One wrong move, and we'll both be charged
with kidnapping and murder.

561
00:48:01,400 --> 00:48:03,610
Still, that doesn't seem right.

562
00:48:04,111 --> 00:48:04,945
If we just

563
00:48:05,821 --> 00:48:08,156
explain that she died because of us--

564
00:48:08,240 --> 00:48:10,701
And who would believe that

565
00:48:10,784 --> 00:48:13,078
when the mastermind up and died?

566
00:48:13,161 --> 00:48:15,580
Then what do we do now?

567
00:48:15,664 --> 00:48:17,416
That's why I'm saying we dump her.

568
00:48:19,292 --> 00:48:20,419
No, I mean…

569
00:48:22,337 --> 00:48:26,091
Chae-ni isn't trash!
How could we just dump her?

570
00:48:26,591 --> 00:48:29,177
Chae-ni is my friend!

571
00:48:29,261 --> 00:48:34,099
No, I don't mean dump her.
I meant that we should hide her.

572
00:48:34,599 --> 00:48:36,977
We'll just lay her to rest temporarily.

573
00:48:41,356 --> 00:48:43,650
Why…

574
00:48:44,609 --> 00:48:45,986
Chae-ni.

575
00:48:47,070 --> 00:48:49,740
Please close your eyes.

576
00:48:50,323 --> 00:48:53,368
Holy smokes, I'm so scared.

577
00:48:53,869 --> 00:48:56,121
Please just close your eyes.

578
00:49:00,292 --> 00:49:03,336
Chae-ni, I'm sorry. Close your eyes…

579
00:49:05,672 --> 00:49:06,715
I'm so scared.

580
00:49:09,634 --> 00:49:10,635
I'm freaking out!

581
00:49:12,971 --> 00:49:14,056
<i>That's right.</i>

582
00:49:14,556 --> 00:49:18,310
<i>The one who orchestrated this kidnapping</i>
<i>that hastened my death</i>

583
00:49:18,852 --> 00:49:20,020
<i>was me, Eun Chae-ni.</i>

584
00:49:20,604 --> 00:49:23,023
You guys are so frustrating, seriously.

585
00:49:23,106 --> 00:49:27,027
You both wear masks, and one of you films
while the other appears on camera with me.

586
00:49:27,110 --> 00:49:29,362
That's all you have to do.
What's the fuss?

587
00:49:29,446 --> 00:49:30,947
That was the 50 million won

588
00:49:31,615 --> 00:49:33,116
you said you'd be getting?

589
00:49:33,617 --> 00:49:34,451
Oh, come on!

590
00:49:35,118 --> 00:49:37,704
I'll receive the money
and give you your shares.

591
00:49:37,788 --> 00:49:39,956
There's no way we'll get caught.

592
00:49:40,040 --> 00:49:41,374
Don't you know I'm smart?

593
00:49:41,875 --> 00:49:43,502
If you can't trust me,

594
00:49:44,044 --> 00:49:44,961
trust my brain.

595
00:49:45,045 --> 00:49:49,549
Isn't it unfair if you get 50 million,
and we only get 5 million won apiece?

596
00:49:49,633 --> 00:49:51,093
Then count yourself out.

597
00:49:51,176 --> 00:49:53,136
Do you want to film or should I?

598
00:49:53,220 --> 00:49:54,763
Seriously?

599
00:49:55,514 --> 00:49:58,100
I'd feel so guilty toward your grandma.

600
00:49:58,183 --> 00:50:00,936
How could we stab her
in the back like this?

601
00:50:01,019 --> 00:50:02,896
Why don't you think it through again?

602
00:50:04,272 --> 00:50:07,275
I'm sure you've built up
more than just debt against Grandma.

603
00:50:09,569 --> 00:50:10,946
Think about it.

604
00:50:11,029 --> 00:50:13,073
All those years of Grandma's bullying.

605
00:50:17,327 --> 00:50:21,164
But why now?
Why do you suddenly want to go on a trip?

606
00:50:22,499 --> 00:50:23,333
Just because.

607
00:50:23,834 --> 00:50:27,212
If I don't go now,
I don't think I'll ever get to go.

608
00:50:28,463 --> 00:50:31,466
That's true.
You'd never earn enough peeling onions.

609
00:50:31,550 --> 00:50:34,261
But still, isn't this a little too…

610
00:50:34,344 --> 00:50:37,222
I'm worried about both your heart
and your grandma.

611
00:50:37,305 --> 00:50:41,685
I left her a letter.
She'll understand once she reads it.

612
00:50:42,769 --> 00:50:45,021
Just help me out, will you?

613
00:50:45,689 --> 00:50:48,066
I'm really excited right now.

614
00:50:49,526 --> 00:50:51,945
I haven't felt this alive in a long time.

615
00:51:10,881 --> 00:51:13,049
Are you sure
you're not just pretending to push?

616
00:51:14,885 --> 00:51:17,888
This is me pushing with all my strength.

617
00:51:18,388 --> 00:51:19,431
So,

618
00:51:20,432 --> 00:51:21,850
where are we gonna dump her?

619
00:51:21,933 --> 00:51:25,437
We're not dumping her. This is temporary!
Temporarily laying her to rest.

620
00:51:25,520 --> 00:51:28,690
Exactly. Where are we gonna dump Chae-ni…

621
00:51:32,068 --> 00:51:32,944
Chae-ni.

622
00:51:34,821 --> 00:51:37,324
Mr. Son, Chae-ni won't close her eyes.

623
00:51:45,624 --> 00:51:46,708
We're here.

624
00:51:47,918 --> 00:51:48,752
This is it.

625
00:51:50,420 --> 00:51:52,005
People rarely come here,

626
00:51:52,714 --> 00:51:54,174
and there are no cameras.

627
00:51:54,674 --> 00:51:57,093
A place the authorities will never look,

628
00:51:57,177 --> 00:51:59,387
abandoned even by its landowner.

629
00:51:59,930 --> 00:52:01,473
A land of tragedy.

630
00:52:01,973 --> 00:52:06,728
Mr. Son, are you sure
we really have to go this far?

631
00:52:11,191 --> 00:52:13,652
Just until we come up with alibis, okay?

632
00:52:14,361 --> 00:52:15,946
Chae-ni will understand.

633
00:52:16,446 --> 00:52:20,158
She wouldn't like it if we were blamed
for something she planned.

634
00:52:21,243 --> 00:52:22,202
Got it?

635
00:52:23,662 --> 00:52:24,496
Let's go.

636
00:52:29,251 --> 00:52:30,085
Be gentle.

637
00:52:35,966 --> 00:52:37,008
Let's switch.

638
00:52:46,851 --> 00:52:47,686
Lift her.

639
00:52:52,524 --> 00:52:54,025
Careful on the way down.

640
00:52:54,734 --> 00:52:55,902
Okay.

641
00:52:56,403 --> 00:52:57,279
All right.

642
00:52:58,029 --> 00:52:59,406
One, two…

643
00:52:59,990 --> 00:53:01,199
Excuse me.

644
00:53:13,503 --> 00:53:14,462
Mr. Son Gyeong-hun?

645
00:53:14,546 --> 00:53:15,463
Yes.

646
00:53:19,801 --> 00:53:21,136
What are you doing here?

647
00:53:23,471 --> 00:53:26,141
You raise daily complaints
about dumping on these grounds,

648
00:53:26,224 --> 00:53:27,851
then dump trash here yourself?

649
00:53:30,854 --> 00:53:33,440
The oddball from City Hall?

650
00:53:34,357 --> 00:53:35,275
Why are you here?

651
00:53:35,358 --> 00:53:38,028
Because someone grumbled
that we weren't doing inspections.

652
00:53:38,111 --> 00:53:40,196
You said it'd be no use even if you did.

653
00:53:41,448 --> 00:53:45,410
That you were stuck without the landowner.
Oh, whatever. Just go.

654
00:53:45,493 --> 00:53:47,245
I'm withdrawing my complaint. Withdrawn.

655
00:53:53,877 --> 00:53:54,711
What's that…

656
00:53:57,005 --> 00:53:57,922
behind you?

657
00:54:04,596 --> 00:54:05,597
What…

658
00:54:36,753 --> 00:54:37,670
What

659
00:54:39,089 --> 00:54:40,048
is that?

660
00:54:50,350 --> 00:54:51,351
A mannequin.

661
00:54:52,560 --> 00:54:53,937
You expect me to believe that?

662
00:55:34,227 --> 00:55:35,562
We didn't kill her!

663
00:56:06,009 --> 00:56:07,343
The two of you…

664
00:56:07,844 --> 00:56:09,762
Were you trying to dispose of a dead body?

665
00:56:10,346 --> 00:56:12,098
Dispose of a body? No, that's not…

666
00:56:12,182 --> 00:56:13,224
We…

667
00:56:14,893 --> 00:56:16,519
You see, we…

668
00:56:16,603 --> 00:56:18,897
At first, we were just pretending
to kidnap her--

669
00:56:18,980 --> 00:56:20,315
A kidnapping and murder?

670
00:56:20,398 --> 00:56:22,942
No, we didn't!

671
00:56:23,485 --> 00:56:25,195
I swear we didn't even touch her.

672
00:56:25,987 --> 00:56:28,239
She just died on her own.

673
00:56:28,823 --> 00:56:30,909
Chae-ni!

674
00:56:32,076 --> 00:56:35,038
Do you think we wanted to do this?

675
00:56:35,121 --> 00:56:37,123
She's our neighbor!

676
00:56:38,291 --> 00:56:42,795
We even know the old lady
who runs Hearty House.

677
00:56:42,879 --> 00:56:45,298
Do you really think we wanted to do this?

678
00:56:45,965 --> 00:56:47,675
By Hearty House, do you mean…

679
00:56:48,259 --> 00:56:50,678
You mean that so-called trainwreck, right?

680
00:56:50,762 --> 00:56:51,721
Yes.

681
00:56:52,805 --> 00:56:54,933
Chae-ni!

682
00:56:57,602 --> 00:56:59,854
Chae-ni!

683
00:57:00,605 --> 00:57:02,941
Chae-ni! Chae…

684
00:57:05,860 --> 00:57:06,694
Chae-ni?

685
00:57:07,779 --> 00:57:09,280
Chae-ni, where did she go?

686
00:57:09,364 --> 00:57:11,157
-Mr. Son, where'd she go?
-Where is she?

687
00:57:11,241 --> 00:57:12,867
Where is she? She was right here.

688
00:57:13,493 --> 00:57:15,787
-Chae-ni. Where?
-Go check over there.

689
00:57:17,705 --> 00:57:18,873
-Chae-ni.
-Chae-ni!

690
00:57:18,957 --> 00:57:20,250
Chae-ni!

691
00:57:20,333 --> 00:57:21,626
-Chae-ni!
-Chae-ni?

692
00:57:21,709 --> 00:57:23,753
-Chae-ni.
-Chae-ni!

693
00:57:24,254 --> 00:57:26,673
Chae-ni.

694
00:57:26,756 --> 00:57:29,676
What's going on here?
Do you have another accomplice?

695
00:57:30,260 --> 00:57:32,595
-No!
-No!

696
00:57:32,679 --> 00:57:35,181
Then where did the body go?
What did you do with it?

697
00:57:36,099 --> 00:57:37,183
Is there someone else?

698
00:57:38,017 --> 00:57:39,686
No, there isn't!

699
00:57:40,687 --> 00:57:42,939
We really didn't do it.

700
00:57:43,523 --> 00:57:47,902
But given the circumstances,
anyone would think that we did it,

701
00:57:48,403 --> 00:57:52,282
so we were just going
to leave her here temporarily.

702
00:57:54,409 --> 00:57:56,661
If you don't tell me,
I'm calling the cops.

703
00:57:56,744 --> 00:57:58,746
-Sir, please.
-Where's your accomplice?

704
00:57:59,956 --> 00:58:00,873
I'll do it.

705
00:58:00,957 --> 00:58:03,042
Mr. Oddball! Just a second.

706
00:58:04,711 --> 00:58:06,588
Just hear me out for a…

707
00:58:06,671 --> 00:58:07,589
Mr. Oddball!

708
00:58:08,840 --> 00:58:10,091
Let go!

709
00:58:13,386 --> 00:58:14,887
No, please.

710
00:58:14,971 --> 00:58:15,847
Let go!

711
00:58:16,347 --> 00:58:19,267
-Let go of me!
-Mr. Oddball, sir.

712
00:58:19,350 --> 00:58:21,060
Sir Oddball, please!

713
00:58:22,520 --> 00:58:24,355
You can't call the cops!

714
00:58:24,981 --> 00:58:26,899
She really did die on her own.

715
00:58:27,525 --> 00:58:29,694
But if you report it
as a kidnapping and murder,

716
00:58:29,777 --> 00:58:31,613
we'll definitely be charged

717
00:58:31,696 --> 00:58:34,115
as the culprits!

718
00:58:34,907 --> 00:58:36,951
<i>Hello?</i>

719
00:58:37,035 --> 00:58:39,871
<i>Hello? Did I just hear you say</i>
<i>a kidnapping and murder?</i>

720
00:58:42,582 --> 00:58:44,125
No!

721
00:58:44,208 --> 00:58:46,085
That's not it!

722
00:58:46,169 --> 00:58:47,920
We're innocent!

723
00:59:07,523 --> 00:59:10,360
<i>This is 112.</i>
<i>We traced your number due to the urgency.</i>

724
00:59:10,443 --> 00:59:13,404
<i>Where are you right now, sir?</i>
<i>Are you safe?</i>

725
00:59:14,322 --> 00:59:15,823
<i>Is this Mr. Lee Un-jeong?</i>

726
00:59:16,324 --> 00:59:17,909
<i>What's the situation right now?</i>

727
00:59:19,869 --> 00:59:23,623
<i>A squad car has been dispatched,</i>
<i>so please hang in there.</i>

728
00:59:23,706 --> 00:59:25,291
A car has been dispatched!

729
00:59:26,084 --> 00:59:28,836
We're done for!

730
00:59:29,796 --> 00:59:32,131
Oh no!

731
00:59:32,799 --> 00:59:34,175
No!

732
00:59:36,552 --> 00:59:43,559
HEARTY HOUSE

733
00:59:49,857 --> 00:59:51,526
-Get out of there.
-I can't.

734
00:59:51,609 --> 00:59:53,361
-Hey, just a moment.
-What's your name?

735
00:59:53,444 --> 00:59:54,696
Don't come closer.

736
00:59:54,779 --> 00:59:56,781
I need your name, sir.

737
00:59:57,782 --> 00:59:59,367
-Get over here.
-Seriously?

738
00:59:59,450 --> 01:00:00,868
Just stay right here, then.

739
01:00:02,036 --> 01:00:03,538
God, it stinks.

740
01:00:04,831 --> 01:00:06,958
Wait, time out!

741
01:00:07,750 --> 01:00:09,877
-Mr. Lee Un-jeong, you called it in?
-Yes.

742
01:00:09,961 --> 01:00:11,337
I told you I didn't do it.

743
01:00:11,421 --> 01:00:15,633
I witnessed those two men
trying to dispose of a woman's dead body.

744
01:00:18,094 --> 01:00:19,345
So where's the body?

745
01:00:19,929 --> 01:00:23,099
I think their accomplice hid it
while they distracted me.

746
01:00:23,182 --> 01:00:24,475
It disappeared.

747
01:00:27,395 --> 01:00:30,022
And the victim was
Ms. Eun Chae-ni of Hearty House?

748
01:00:31,149 --> 01:00:31,983
Yes.

749
01:00:32,608 --> 01:00:33,651
I believe so.

750
01:00:33,735 --> 01:00:35,903
Are you talking about that woman
over there?

751
01:00:38,698 --> 01:00:40,658
Yes, that's right.

752
01:00:58,301 --> 01:01:00,136
Isn't that Chae-ni?

753
01:01:21,991 --> 01:01:22,825
<i>I…</i>

754
01:01:24,619 --> 01:01:25,495
<i>That woman…</i>

755
01:01:27,038 --> 01:01:28,831
<i>was definitely dead.</i>

756
01:01:55,107 --> 01:01:56,609
Let go!

757
01:06:08,444 --> 01:06:13,449
Subtitle translation by: Jimin Choi

